{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["UV Pelt"], "type": "title", "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "text": ["Relaxes UVs by pulling them out toward the edges of the texture area."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["UV Pelt operates very similar to how a tanner\ncreates a pelt. Cuts are made to the geometry to produce a surface\ntopologically equivalent to a disc. The boundaries of this surface are\nconnected to a frame and stretched out."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["Any closed face can be used as a frame for the pelt. A circle is used if\nno frame is specified. A hint polygon is used to specify which section\nof the geometry to pelt after performing the cuts. The longest boundary of \nthe section containing the hint polygon is the one connected to the \nframe. The frame is parameterized to the range ", {"text": ["[0, 1)"], "type": "code"}, ". The boundary points \nare spaced around the frame at distances in the frame\u2019s parameterization\nthat are proportional to the edge length with the neighboring boundary\npoint."]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The effect of this operation is best visualized in the UV viewport,\n    or with textures turned on in the 3D viewport."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Corresponds to distance on the geometry."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["XYZ"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Corresponds to distance in UVW (texture) space."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["UVW"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Ignores the third dimension in texture space."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["UV"]}], "type": "dt_group", "container": true}], "type": "pxml", "tag": "div", "indent": 0, "attrs": {"id": "visualizePara"}}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["UV Pelt creates the UV vertex texture attribute if it does not already exist."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["UV Pelt only operates on polygons. Other geometry type such as Bezier\n    and NURBS surfaces can be converted to polygons using a Convert\n    operation prior to applying UV Pelt."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "text": ["Click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/uvpelt", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/uvpelt"}, {"text": ["UV Pelt"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/uvpelt", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/uvpelt"}, " tool on the ", {"text": ["Texture"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["You can easily select loops of edges using the ", {"text": ["Edge Loop"], "fullpath": "/shelf/edgeloop", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/edgeloop"}, " tool."]}], "indent": 8, "role": "item", "type": "tip"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "tip_group"}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_select.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_select.png"}]}], "indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "text": ["Select the edges that will form the boundary of the pelt."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_after.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_after.png"}]}], "indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "text": ["Press ", {"keys": ["Enter"], "text": null, "type": "keys"}, " to unwrap your selection.  "]}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["You can scale the pelt by increasing the ", {"text": ["Boundary Springs"], "type": "ui"}, " in the ", {"text": ["parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/parms", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/ref/panes/parms"}, ". You can also use ", {"text": ["UV Edit"], "fullpath": "/shelf/uvedit", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "uvedit"}, " to move the UVs."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Using UV Pelt"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "includeme"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["The name of the texture coordinate attribute to pelt, defaulting to ", {"text": ["uv"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["UV Attribute"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "uvattrib"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Edges to cut."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Edge Cut Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/group"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Every edge is modeled as a spring. The points are placed to the position that minimizes the spring energy. The choice of Pelting Method affects the strength of individual springs."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "text": ["Uses spring weights based on length of the edges and the areas of a the faces incident to the edge. "]}, {"indent": 16, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/uv/uvpelt1.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/uv/uvpelt1.png"}]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["Spring Relaxation"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "text": ["Uses unit weights except at boundary points. This means that every point is placed at the mass center of its neighbors. The mass of the boundary points is given by the spring parameter. The main advantage of this method is that it always guarantees a one-to-one parametrization (with no inverted triangles) for convex boundaries. "]}, {"indent": 16, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/uv/uvpelt2.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/uv/uvpelt2.png"}]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["Tutte Barycentric"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "text": ["Uses a weight assignment scheme known as discrete harmonic method which minimizes angular distortion. "]}, {"indent": 16, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/uv/uvpelt3.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/uv/uvpelt3.png"}]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["Discrete Harmonic"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Pelting Method"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/method"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Indicates a primitive group should be created for the polygons\n        making up the the pelt."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Create Output Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/outputtoggle"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Name of the primitive group to create."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Output Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/outputgroup"}, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Specifies the number of iterations of the algorithm for\n            solving the UV positions."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Iterations"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/iters"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["The strength of the springs connecting the pelt boundary to\n            the frame."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Boundary Springs"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/k"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Specifies an attribute of the input geometry\u2019s points that\n            will be used to scale the strength of the springs connected\n            to the point."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Stiffness Attribute"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/stiffness"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["The primitive specifying which section of the geometry forms\n            the pelt."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Hint Primitive"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/hintprim"}, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Pelt"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["The primitive to use for the frame."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Frame"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/frame"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["The attribute of the frame used for the U coordinate."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["U From"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/ufrom"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["The attribute of the frame used for the V coordinate."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["V From"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/vfrom"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Indicates the UV coordinates should be moved to the ranges\n            specified with U Range and V Range."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Use Range"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/userange"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["The location of the left and right edges, respectively, of\n            the texture"]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["U Range"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/urange"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["The location of the bottom and top edges, respectively, of\n            the texture"]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["V Range"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/vrange"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Specifies where on the frame to position the first boundary\n            point (the boundary point closest to the hint polygon)."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Orientation"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/orientation"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Specifies an attribute of the frame\u2019s points that will guide\n            the process of connecting boundary points to the frame."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Weight Attribute"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/weight"}, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Frame"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/uvproject", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/uvproject"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/uvquickshade", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/uvquickshade"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/texture", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/texture"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/uvunwrap", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/uvunwrap"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["UV Pelt"], "summary": ["Relaxes UVs by pulling them out toward the edges of the texture area."], "attrs": {"version": "2.0", "tags": "uvs, textures, cleanup", "namespace": null, "internal": "uvpelt", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/uvpelt"}, "included": ["/nodes/sop/texture_common", "/shelf/uvpelt"], "type": "root"}